name: jsnad
description: ## About how to install and not Node.js - Do not install Node with OS package managers.   - It tends to lag the fast Node.js release cycle.   - Binary and config files could not be standardized causing compatibility issues.   - Installing global modules required `sudo`, this is not ideal since it grants root privileges to third party libraries. - The recommend way to install Node is using a version package management, on our case `nvm`.
